# Studio Frontend (`apps/web`)

## Feature layout

```
src/features/
  studio/     Timeline, canvas (Konva), tools dock, filmstrip, export, menubar
  translation/  Transcribe/translate/voiceover (prefer services/ai-content via api.*)
  project/    useAppStore + useStudioProject (API load/poll/save)
  projects/   Recent projects list
  upload/     Video upload + blank project create
  settings/   Theme, i18n preferences
  landing/    Marketing sections, what's new
```

## Editor core (Omniclip reference)

Reference: https://github.com/omni-media/omniclip

Use Omniclip for **editor core behavior**, not visuals:

- Timeline/clip mental model: trim, split, transitions, effects
- Undo/redo and project-level state updates
- Preview interactions (move/resize/style) on canvas

**Always keep Vokop’s own CapCut-style UI/UX**: app menubar, tools rail, near-black studio shell, custom export/launch buttons. Do not install or render Omniclip web components as the product UI.

## Studio tools (CapCut-style rail)

`media | text | audio | voice | captions | effects | transitions | filters` (+ AI clip)

- Presets from `useEditorCatalog()` + apply via `useEditorActions()`.
- Filter preview: CSS on `<video>` via `getVideoCssFilter()` in store.
- Server apply/preview when `videoSessionId` exists (`useVideoSession` on studio load).
- **Studio AI** (transcribe, translate, TTS, text assist, image, clips, agent) → `services/ai-content` via `/api/v1/ai/*` and `ApiClient` (`api.translate`, `api.startTranscribe`, `api.synthesizeSpeech`, `api.assistText`, `api.analyzeImage`, `api.suggestClips`, `api.runAgent`). Prefer server APIs over client-only Gemini in `features/translation/`.

## State

- **useAppStore**: video file, timeline, canvas elements, `projectId`, `projectEditor`.
- **useStudioProject**: loads `/projects/:id`, polls while `processing`, debounced PATCH for name/aspect ratio.
- **Server session**: `videoSessionId` set after `api.createVideoSession()`; cleared on new video.

## API client

```typescript
import { api } from '@/lib/api';
// Dev proxy: /api → gateway :4000
// AI: api.getAiCapabilities(), api.translate(...), api.waitForAiJob(jobId)
```

## UI

- Prefer reusable primitives from `@vokop/ui`; move stable cross-app UI there instead of duplicating components in `apps/web`.
- Import Ant Design widgets from `@vokop/ui/antd` (e.g. `Popover`, `Select`, `Modal`) — do not add `antd` as a direct app dependency.
- Import shadcn/Radix-style primitives from `@vokop/ui/shadcn` when needed for custom product UI.
- Keep one-off visual customization in the owning feature/component. Promote it to `packages/ui` only when it is reusable across apps.
- Button hover: color/opacity only — no transform scale/translate (see `button-interactions` rule).
